name: Thubten Nyandak Rinpoche
messages_slogans: Central Tibet Administration released a report on May 27, 2013 confirming reports that they have self-immolated for Tibet.

name: Tenzin Khedup
messages_slogans: "carrying Tibetan flags and shouting pro-independence slogans"

name: Ngawang Norphel
messages_slogans: "carrying Tibetan flags and shouting pro-independence slogans"

name: Choepa

name: Lobsang Kelsang
messages_slogans: "It is not known what he shouted or said as he set himself on fire."

name: Lobsang Damchoe
messages_slogans: "It is not known what he shouted or said as he set himself on fire."

name: Pasang Lhamo
messages_slogans: In reports emerging after 4 months it is reported that Pasang Lhamo, 63, self-immolated in China_„_Í Í‰s capital city of Beijing in September 2012. She is believed to have set herself on fire in protest against illegal land grabbing by Chinese authorities in the Keygudo region of eastern Tibet following the devastating 2010 earthquake. According to the Dharamshala based Central Tibetan Administration, Passang Lhamo, a 62-year-old native of Keygudo torched herself on September 13, 2012 after _„_Í Í_repeated appeals to the central authorities in Beijing failed to yield any concrete results._„_Í Í_  Passang Lhamo was forced to head to Beijing after local authorities in Keygudo refused to allow her to retain her ancestral home following the major rebuilding process in the region. She was reportedly taken to hospital where she was treated for "severe burn injuries."

name: Tamdin Dorje
family_status: grandfather of the 7th Gungthang Rinpoche, wife, 3 grown children

name: Tsering Dhondup
messages_slogans: Dhondup often talked to young people, and recently expressed the view that if Tibetans need to self-immolate, then it should be the older generation. An exiled Tibetan from Labrang said: "He used to say that we had a very difficult life under the Chinese authorities, saying that the Chinese torture us and look down on us. He said to young people that their lives were really important to Tibet_„_Í Í‰s future."

name: Dorjee Rinchen
family_status: Wife Tabho, son, daughter, mother in her 80s
messages_slogans: Appointed local Tibetan leader. Highly respected in his community.

name: Tsepo
tibetan_area: Nagrog Phampa Village, Driru, north of Lhasa
messages_slogans: Shouted sloagans for independence and the return of the Dalai Lama to Tibet

name: Tenzin
tibetan_area: Nagrog Phampa Village, Driru, north of Lhasa
messages_slogans: Shouted sloagans for independence and the return of the Dalai Lama to Tibet

name: Lhamo Tseten
family_status: parents, young wife Tsering, two-year old daughter
messages_slogans: He shouted that His Holiness the Dalai Lama should come back to Tibet, and that Tibet should be free. He was reportedly still shouting when he collapsed with his hands clasped in prayer.

name: Thupwang Kyab
messages_slogans: Local people covered his body with khatas and took him home.

name: Dorjee Lhundrup
messages_slogans: Many people gathered where he staged his protest and protected his corpse from Chinese police and troops.  He was then taken to the monastery where monks and laypeople prayed for him. He was later cremated in a spot behind the monastery where only high lamas are traditionally cremated.

name: Tamdin Tso
family_status: Mother of 1 son, Nyingjam Tsering, aged 5 or 6, and her father, Tamdrin Kyab, and mother, Konchog Tso.

name: Tsegyu (Tsegyal)
family_status: Father of two (six and an 18-month-old infant)
messages_slogans: _„_Í Í_For less than two weeks, from November 7 to 18, Tsegyal received no treatment for his burns while being held at the local police station in Nagchu town,_„_Í Í_ TCHRD said citing sources. _„_Í Í_Tsegyal died in the evening of November 18 in police custody._„_Í Í_

name: Nyankar Tashi
family_status: Wife Drugmo Tso, 23, and father, Tashi Namgyal, 47
messages_slogans: Set fire to himself today during a prayer ceremony held in Dowa Township for a young mother, who self-immolated last on 7 November. Nyingkar Tashi, the seventh Tibetan to set himself on fire in the past six days, is reported to have died at the scene. He called out for freedom in Tibet and the long life of the Dalai Lama.

name: Nyingchag Bum
family_status: Eldest of 4 siblings in his family; father Sangchug, 44, and mother Tsering Tso, 38,
messages_slogans: In a note he wrote, "Tibet needs freedom and independence. Release Panchen and let Dalai return home. I self-immolate to protest against the Chinese government! Father, please don't be disheartened because of me. I follow the Buddha and Goodness. My wish is that six million Tibetans will learn their mother tongue, wear Tibetan clothes and be united."

name: Tenzin Dolma
messages_slogans: The incident coincided with the appointment of the leader Xi Jinping of the Communist party of China. Hundreds of local Tibetans attended a cremation ceremony for Tingzin Dolma. Her last words to her father, "Father, being a Tibetan is so difficult. We can't even say our prayer to Dalai Lama's portrait. We have no freedom at all_„_Í ‘_"

name: Kharbum Gyal
family_status: Father, Tamdin Gyal, and mother Dolkar Tso, and 6 siblings.

name: Chagmo Kyi
messages_slogans: Local lay Tibetans and monks gathered to mark Chagmo Kyi's death despite an intense military buildup in the area following peaceful protests and other self-immolations over the past week. According to Tibetan sources hundreds of Tibetans attended her cremation, at a site normally used for the cremation of monks and lamas. They were surrounded by troops.

name: Sangdak Tsering
messages_slogans: In a Note he wrote, "There is no freedom in Tibet, His Holiness Dalai Lama is forbidden to return home. Panchen Lama [the second highest ranking Lama after the Dalai Lama] is in prison. Numerous Tibetan heroes have made the sacrifice of self-immolation. I don't want to live anymore, there is no meaning in living_„_Í ‘_ We are the son of Snow Lion, the offspring of red face Tibetans. Please remember the dignity of Snow mountain."

name: Wangchen Norbu
messages_slogans: Norbu had been present at a Nov. 8 prayer gathering at the monastery for other Tibetan self-immolations who have lost their lives in anti-China protests. _„_Í Í_He became emotional when he saw many elderly Tibetan mourners faint from grief,_„_Í Í_ a source said. Shouted slogans calling for the return of the Dalai Lama to Tibet, release of the Panchen Lama and freedom for Tibet. Around 10:30 pm local time, the crowds are reported to have shouted slogans calling for the return of the exiled spiritual leader the Dalai Lama to Tibet. The gathering of monks and local people are reported to have been reciting long life prayers for the Dalai Lama.

name: Tsering Dhondup/Dundrup
family_status: Mother is Drukmo Tso, father is Lubum Gyal. Wife Tamdin Tso and 2 children.
messages_slogans: Tsering Dundrup set fire to himself around 9:00am and he was in his thirties. Tsering Dundrup was both a farmer and nomad and he is from Chungan village in Amchok Shang, Labrang [Chinese: Xiahe county], Ganlho prefecture, Gansu province. Tsering Dondrub was known for his _„_Í Í_gentle character_„_Í Í_ and devotion to the Tibetan cause.

name: Tamdrin Dorjee
family_status: He was the breadwinner of a family of 6
messages_slogans: He was heard shouting for the long life of the Dalai Lama, with his hands together as if in prayer.

name: Tamdrin Kyab
family_status: 3 brothers, one of whom is a monk
messages_slogans: He self-immolated at night, and locals were not aware of his self-immolation until they found his charred body the next morning.

name: Wangyal
family_status: Orphan, with three brothers and one sister.
messages_slogans: Eyewitnesses say his hands were clasped in prayers as he ran raising slogans for the return of His Holiness the Dalai Lama and freedom for the Tibetan people.

name: Kunchok Tsering
family_status: Wife, Sangay Tso, 19 and parents Phagkyab, 40 and Gonpo Tso, 37, and an elder brother.
messages_slogans: He burned himself at the same mining site where Tsering Dhondup died after his self-immolation on November 20. Amchok monastery monks and a large number of local Tibetans are known to have gathered at the deceased_„_Í Í‰s home to offer prayers.

name: Gonpo Tsering
family_status: Wife, three children all below the age of six, and parents.

name: Kalsang Kyab
messages_slogans: Protested infront of the Kyangtsa govt. office.Approaching the government office, he poured petrol on himself and started shouting slogans, then set fire to himself as he reached the entrance. He continued repeating slogans - _„_Í Í_May the Dalai Lama live for 100 aeons! May Kirti Rinpoche live for 100 aeons!_„_Í Í_  It is believed that he spoke about his intention to commit self-immolation protest to a few people in previous days, but no-one paid much attention to this.

name: Sangye Tashi
messages_slogans: According to reports Sangay Tashi shouted slogans calling for the return of His Holiness the Dalai Lama and the release of all Tibetan political prisoners, including the 11th Panchen Lama, while engulfed in flames. Local Tibetans then carried his charred body to a nearby house. He arrived in Sangkhog town earlier that day with his friends. Before setting himself on fire, he reportedly called one of his relatives and told him that he had decided to set himself on fire for the cause of Tibet. Before his relative could carry on the conversation, Sangay Tashi hung up the phone and switched it off.

name: Wande Khar (or Bendey Khar according to a local)
Tsering Namgyal
messages_slogans: _„_Í Í_Tsering Namgyal set himself on fire near the local Chinese government office in Luchu earlier today for the cause of Tibet,_„_Í Í_ Sonam, a Tibetan monk living in south India told Phayul, citing sources in the region. _„_Í Í_Tsering Tashi passed in his fiery protest._„_Í Í_

name: Kunchok Kyap
messages_slogans: Died on 1 December in Barkham. His relatives were given only a portion of his ashes. Tibetans from the Dzoge region and beyond, monks and laypeople, young and old alike are still coming to greet his family members, to mourn and express their sympathy and solidarity.

name: Sangdag Kyap
messages_slogans: Sungdue Kyab reportedly carried out his self-immolation protest in the afternoon today on the main street in Bora town near the Bora Monastery. Soon after he set himself on fire, Chinese security personnel arrived at the site of his protest, doused the flames and bundled him away. He is believed to have survived his protest.

name: Kunchok Phelgye
family_status: Nine members in his family. His parents are Kunchok Kyab and Dolma Tso.
messages_slogans: Kunchok Phelgye was enveloped in flames and his hands were joined in prayers as he raised slogans for the long life and return of His Holiness the Dalai Lama and Kyabje Kirti Rinpoche, the exiled head of Kirti Monastery,_„_Í Í_ the release said citing sources in the region. _„_Í Í_He also raised slogans calling for the return and reunification of Tibetans. Kunchok Phelgye succumbed to his injuries at the site of his protest. Monks of the Monastery surrounded Kunchok Phelgye_„_Í Í‰s burning body and began to recite the prayer. Later, Kunchok Phelgye_„_Í Í‰s body was carried to his quarters in the Monastery where hundreds of monks and local Tibetans continue to visit to offer their last respects and prayers.

name: Pema Dorjee
messages_slogans: Pema Dorjee raised slogans calling for the return of His Holiness the Dalai Lama, independence of Tibet, unity of Tibetans and for the land of Tibet to be ruled by Tibetans,_„_Í Í_ Sonam said citing a contact in the region.

name: Wangchen Kyi
messages_slogans: Around two thousand Tibetans gathered at the site of her protest and raised slogans calling for His Holiness the Dalai Lama_„_Í Í‰s long life and reciting his long life prayers,_„_Í Í_ Sonam said citing sources in the region. _„_Í Í_The crowd was emotionally charged and many of them were crying.

name: Tsering Tashi
messages_slogans: _„_Í Í_Tsebhe set himself on fire in Amchok town at around 1 pm (local time),_„_Í Í_ Ajam said. _„_Í Í_He succumbed to his injuries at the protest site following which local Tibetans were able to rescue his body from falling into the hands of Chinese security personnel._„_Í Í_

name: Sonam Dhargye
family_status: Father, Tsering Dhondup and Mother, Takho

name: Tsesung Kyab
family_status: Cousin of Pema Dorjee, who immolated on 8 December

name: Kunchok Wangmo
messages_slogans: News of the burning was hushed up by Chinese police who had grabbed her body, cremated it and handed over the remains to her family, the sources said.Her husband, Dolma Kyab, was detained when he refused to comply with an order by the Chinese authorities who wanted to blame the self-immolation on a family squabble, one exiled Tibetan with contacts in the region told RFA's Tibetan Service."The authorities wanted Dolma Kyab to declare that she burnt herself as a result of a family conflict and when he refused to comply, he was detained and taken away," Dzoge Lekshek said.

name: Lobsang Thokmey
messages_slogans: He joined Kirti monastery as a child and was in his 8th year of Buddhist studies  according to the traditional monastic system. Thokmey is known to be a role model for younger monks as an excellent scholar and for his socially conscious activities within his community.

name: Kalkyi
messages_slogans: Thirty-year-old Kal Kyi, a mother of four has set herself ablaze protesting near Jonang monastery in Zamthang in Eastern Tibet at 3:30 pm (local time). _„_Í Í_The local Tibetans carried her charred body inside the monastery premises to prevent it from falling into the hands of Chinese security personnel,_„_Í Í‰ said Tsangyang Gyatso, an exile Tibetan who has close contacts in the region. Kal Kyi had died from injuries. Kyi is survived by her husband, Gyepo, and their four children.

name: Wangchen Dolma
messages_slogans: The nun, identified as 21-year-old Wangchen Dolma, succumbed to her burn injuries at a hospital in Dartsedo county on 14 June. The authorities have surreptitiously cremated the body at the hospital. They have also kept the family members of the deceased under house arrest. On the day before of her self-immolation protest, she reportedly advised students of a school in Tawu county to study the Tibetan language well. The name and other details of the nun could not be known in the immediate aftermath of her self-immolation due to severe restrictions imposed on the phone and Internet lines. Wangchen Dolma was born to Tenzin (father) and Youdon (mother) of Gyal Bum Tsang family in Dragthok village in Minyag Drapa region of Tawu County. She was enrolled at a Buddhist institute located on Barshab Dragkar, a sacred hill near her village.

name: Konchok Sonam
messages_slogans: Prayers were held for Konchok Sonam after his self-immolation despite the authorities_„_Í Í‰ attempts to prevent Tibetans doing so, according to exile Tibetan sources.Kunchok Sonam was regarded as _„_Í Í_exceptional_„_Í Í‰ in his studies. He had told friends that living under Chinese rule in Tibet had brought too much suffering.

name: Shichung
messages_slogans: When Tibetans gathered around his body, police aimed their guns at the crowd. Village elders averted tensions by appealing to both local Tibetans and police for calm. Forty-year old Shichung set himself on fire outside his house and ran along the road shouting in protest against the Chinese authorities before he collapsed to the ground in flames and died, according to Kirti monks in exile in Dharamsala. The monks said before he self-immolated, he lit a butter-lamp before an image of the Dalai Lama. A few days earlier, he had said, _„_Í Í_The Chinese will never leave us in peace_„_Í Í_, according to the same sources.

name: Jigme Tenzin
tibetan_area: Sonag monastery in Tsekhog county's Jador township
messages_slogans: Monks who carry out funeral rites arrested and beaten.

name: Lhamo Tashi
messages_slogans: A Tibetan student, Lhamo Tashi, set fire to himself and has died on September 17 outside a government Public Security Bureau headquarters in Tsoe City, northeastern Tibet, where he was studying. After setting himself on fire at around midnight, Lhamo Tashi was taken away by police in Tsoe City, the capital of Kanlho (Chinese: Gannan) Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture in Gansu Province (the Tibetan area of Amdo).

name: Kunchok
messages_slogans: 42 year-old Kunchok set himself on fire outside a police station in the Golok (Chinese: Guoluo) Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture in Qinghai Province on 16 September 16. Loca. Tibetans managed to extinguish the flames and Kunchok was rushed to hospital. It is reported that he "was deeply distressed that he had survived" his protest. News of the protest only reached Tibetans in exile o 5 October due to restrictions on information and tightened security in the area. Kunchok is hospitalised.

name: Sangyal Khar
messages_slogans: Tibetan dies after setting self on fire http://www.phayul.com/news/article.aspx?article=Breaking%3A+Tibetan+dies+after+setting+self+on+fire&id=35565
